http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/Youth-found-dead/article13996190.ece

A young man was found dead with multiple injuries near Aloka, on the outskirts of the city, on Tuesday morning.The police said the deceased, identified as Shivalingu (27) a resident of Mahadevapura, appeared to have suffered blows on his head from a concrete chimney pipe, the pieces of which were found near the body.A motorcycle, he was apparently riding, was found near the body.Passers-by alerted the Yelwal police, who shifted the body to Mysore Medical College and Research Institute for a post mortem.The Yelwal police have registered a case and are investigating.